                            <comment id="13420968" author="mmerli" created="Mon, 23 Jul 2012 22:17:29 +0100"  >&lt;p&gt;Attached patch with test case showing the issue&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13422018" author="hustlmsp" created="Wed, 25 Jul 2012 06:37:13 +0100"  >&lt;p&gt;thanks Matteo. the fix is clear, but I had some comments on the test case.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;1. It is not a good idea to put the test in TestReadTimeout. from the name of &apos;TestReadTimeout&apos;, it was used to test read timeout cases. it would be better to put the test case in other test cases like BookKeeperTest.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;2. &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;div class=&quot;code panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;codeContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre class=&quot;code-java&quot;&gt;
+    @Test
+    void testAsyncReadWithError() &lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;throws&lt;/span&gt; Exception {
+        LedgerHandle lh = bkc.createLedger(3, 3, DigestType.CRC32, &lt;span class=&quot;code-quote&quot;&gt;&quot;testPasswd&quot;&lt;/span&gt;.getBytes());
+        stopBKCluster();
&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;p&gt;I think the runtime exception is thrown due the sheduler is closed when closing BookKeeper client. so actually you could just close BookKeeper client only instead of stopping bookkeeper cluster.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13506261" author="hustlmsp" created="Thu, 29 Nov 2012 06:40:30 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/ViewProfile.jspa?name=merlimat&quot; class=&quot;user-hover&quot; rel=&quot;merlimat&quot;&gt;Matteo Merli&lt;/a&gt; Is there any updates about this JIRA?&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13508440" author="mmerli" created="Mon, 3 Dec 2012 02:55:05 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;2nd version of the patch&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13508441" author="mmerli" created="Mon, 3 Dec 2012 02:57:19 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/ViewProfile.jspa?name=hustlmsp&quot; class=&quot;user-hover&quot; rel=&quot;hustlmsp&quot;&gt;Sijie Guo&lt;/a&gt; I&apos;ve updated the test case with the above suggestions. Thanks for reminding this, I had it forgotten.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13508479" author="hustlmsp" created="Mon, 3 Dec 2012 05:21:42 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;the patch lgtm +1. Thanks Matteo.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
